❄️☀️ Is it a funding winter or summer? Honestly… we don’t chase seasons — we back substance.

At Titan Capital, we’ve stayed steady — no matter the funding climate. Why? Because we don’t chase hype cycles or time markets. We back founders building real, enduring businesses with clarity, discipline, and customer obsession.

Whether it’s boom or bust outside, the fundamentals inside these companies remain the same: strong unit economics, clear P&L, and razor-sharp focus.
Capital is just a tool — not a crutch.
#BuiltToLast #StartupInvesting #TitanCapital

Sometimes, life throws you off a perfectly laid path — and that detour becomes your destiny. 
What felt like a setback back then, was actually a setup for everything that followed. I had plans. A roadmap. A timeline. But fate had other ideas.

Years ago, just as I was settling into life at a dream job in the U.S., a two-line email arrived — my H1B visa had been rejected. In a moment, the roadmap I had meticulously built for my future vanished. I packed my bags and came back to India, unsure of what was next.

That visa rejection felt like a setback… until it turned out to be the catalyst that launched my entrepreneurial journey in India. Looking back, I’m grateful it happened.

Today, as the world debates immigration, borders, and who gets access to opportunity — I’m reminded that talent doesn’t need to leave home to build something extraordinary. We can build here. We can thrive here. We can lead from here.

India is no longer just a talent exporter. It’s a builder’s ground. And for many of us, the Plan B became the Best plan. 🇮🇳

🎬 𝗙𝗿𝗼𝗺 𝗗𝗣𝗦 𝗥𝗞 𝗣𝘂𝗿𝗮𝗺 𝘁𝗼 𝘁𝗵𝗲 𝗦𝗵𝗮𝗿𝗸 𝗧𝗮𝗻𝗸 𝘀𝗲𝘁! 🦈✨
Sometimes life comes full circle in the most unexpected ways. I recently met @vineetasng and @sahibabali on the set of @sharktank.india —and guess what? We’re all DPS R.K. Puram alumni! 🤯

From shared memories of badminton courts, canteen breaks, and engineering exam prep stress… to now building and Investing in India’s most promising startups. What are the odds? 🙌

We spoke about hustle, long-term journeys, and how hard work (not shortcuts) is the real compounding factor. 20 years later, some things have changed—but the values we learned in school stayed with us. 💼💡

Here’s to building, remembering, and believing that God truly has a plan for everyone. 💚

India has the talent, tech, and intent to lead in modern defense.

From ancient glory to modern innovation – India is getting back to where it belongs. Our history shows we’ve been a top global economy, and today, as we build the future, it’s time for Indian startups to power the next wave of defence technology. The vision is clear: India must lead in next-gen defence, and we have the talent, technology, and intent to do it.

#IndiaRising #DefenceTech #Innovation #Startups

🚀 𝗜𝗻𝗱𝗶𝗮’𝘀 𝗗𝗲𝗳𝗲𝗻𝗰𝗲 𝗶𝘀 𝗴𝗲𝘁𝘁𝗶𝗻𝗴 𝗮 𝘀𝘁𝗮𝗿𝘁𝘂𝗽 𝘂𝗽𝗴𝗿𝗮𝗱𝗲!

For decades, defence innovation meant big contracts with legacy players. But times have changed. Indian startups are now building faster, cheaper, and better—from advanced drones to next-gen AI systems—right here in Bharat.
The government’s push, combined with startup agility and cost-effectiveness, is creating a new era of self-reliance and innovation in defence. 🇮🇳

This is the 𝗕𝗵𝗮𝗿𝗮𝘁 𝗙𝗶𝗿𝘀𝘁 mindset—where we don’t just buy, we build for India, with India.

Let’s embrace the change. Let’s build the future, together. 💪

Everyone’s chasing unicorns, but what if that’s the wrong goal? Kunal Bahl,Co-founder of Titan Capital & Snapdeal flips the script and introduces the idea of the Indicorn: a business that’s profitable, does ₹100 crore in revenue and was built in the last 15 years. 

Because success isn’t about a big valuation from one investor. It’s about building something that lasts and earns.

#EntrepreneurMindset #StartupJourney #LongTermThinking #Founders #BuildToLast

For too long we have been relying on expensive skincare products that do not work. ‘Miracle’ creams that are more marketing gimmicks.
It’s time we took our skincare seriously.
It’s time to Be Clinical.

Humbled to share that 𝗥𝗼𝗵𝗶𝘁 𝗕𝗮𝗻𝘀𝗮𝗹 and I have been featured in the 𝗦𝗲𝗲𝗱 𝟭𝟬𝟬: 𝗧𝗵𝗲 𝗕𝗲𝘀𝘁 𝗘𝗮𝗿𝗹𝘆-𝗦𝘁𝗮𝗴𝗲 𝗜𝗻𝘃𝗲𝘀𝘁𝗼𝗿𝘀 𝗼𝗳 𝟮𝟬𝟮𝟱 — 𝗮 𝗴𝗹𝗼𝗯𝗮𝗹 𝗹𝗶𝘀𝘁 𝗯𝘆 𝗕𝘂𝘀𝗶𝗻𝗲𝘀𝘀 𝗜𝗻𝘀𝗶𝗱𝗲𝗿, celebrating investors who partner with founders at the very beginning of their journeys.

Even more special — 𝗧𝗶𝘁𝗮𝗻 𝗖𝗮𝗽𝗶𝘁𝗮𝗹 is the only India-focused seed investor on this prestigious list.

Grateful to all the amazing founders we’ve had the good fortune to partner with — your ambition, courage, and resilience inspire us every day. And a big thank you to the incredible 𝗧𝗶𝘁𝗮𝗻 𝗖𝗮𝗽𝗶𝘁𝗮𝗹 team who make it all happen behind the scenes. 🙏🏼

We’ve always believed in backing founders at Day 0 — sometimes before there’s even a product — when it’s just belief, clarity of purpose, and raw determination.

India’s startup ecosystem is just getting started, and we’re excited to play a small part in shaping its future.

The next viral consumer brand? India’s own LLM? Or an app that talks to you about your favourite food and orders it for you?

At #IGFMumbai, Kunal Bahl, Co-Founder of Titan Capital and Snapdeal, offered a grounded perspective on the ongoing debate around deep-tech versus consumer startups. 

Here’s what Shark Kunal Bahl said, “In India, we have businesses that solve different problems. We must celebrate all of them. That said, we should also be pushing the boundaries and widening the aperture of the ecosystem. If we want to have deep-tech innovations, steps will be needed over the long run and it won’t happen overnight.” 

In a world hungry for innovation, how can ecosystems strike the balance between scale, speed, and depth?
